# Database Schema

## Overview

The database is a single Postgres instance on Supabase (project ID dcilltzgegqsrgatskhz, region aws-1-ap-southeast-2). All application tables live in the public schema. Row Level Security is enabled on every table and enforced at the database level — even if the frontend has bugs, data access is gated by RLS policies that read from auth.uid() and the helper functions is_admin(), is_staff(), is_approved(), current_role(), current_status(), current_unit(), is_unit_owner(), is_unit_owner_any().

This document mirrors the actual live schema at the time of writing (post-migration 67, validated against information_schema.columns, pg_proc, pg_policies and information_schema.triggers). When schema changes, update this file.

**Unversioned live objects (important).** A set of objects added during the Community/Wall/Oss arc (V1_3) was applied directly in the Supabase SQL Editor and never saved as numbered migration files: the table `wall_reactions` (+ its `wall_reactions_select` policy), the policy `promotions_select_adult_peer`, and the RPCs `toggle_oss` and `set_event_participation`. They are live in production but absent from `supabase/*.sql`. A rebuild of the database from the migration files alone (for example, the planned `mybjj-staging` project) would NOT recreate them. Backlog item: extract these into migration files (58+) before the staging environment is stood up.

## Tables

### users

The application-level user record, linked 1:1 with auth.users via id. Created by claim_profile() on first authentication.

| Column | Type | Null | Default | Notes |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| id | uuid | NO | - | PK, mirrors auth.users.id |
| email | text | NO | - | Lowercase, login identity |
| full_name | text | YES | - | Display name. Canonical display column; kept in sync from first_name + last_name on self-edit and via the staff/student name-sync triggers |
| first_name | text | YES | - | Two-field input for parent self-edit (migration 54) |
| last_name | text | YES | - | Two-field input for parent self-edit (migration 54) |
| role | text | NO | - | owner, admin (instructor), student, parent |
| unit_id | uuid | YES | FK units.id | Home academy |
| status | text | NO | 'pending' | pending, approved, rejected |
| created_at | timestamptz | NO | now() |  |
| photo_url | text | YES | - | Approved profile photo path in Storage |
| has_password | boolean | NO | false | Tracks whether user has set a password. Source of truth for the 2-step login routing. |
| notification_preferences | jsonb | NO | '{}' | Opt-out model. Keys: feedback, promotions, admin_messages. Photo events bypass prefs. (migration 26/42) |
| phone | text | YES | - | Parent/user self-managed contact phone (migration 53). claim_profile returns the full users row so the client picks it up via S.profile.phone |
| welcome_dismissed | boolean | NO | false | First-session welcome screen dismissal flag (migration 52). Default false; set true on skip or complete |

**Notes**: role='admin' historically means instructor. The string instructor is also accepted but admin is canonical for application checks (the is_admin() helper checks role in ('owner','admin')).

**Name split (migration 54):** full_name remains the canonical display column. first_name/last_name were added for the parent self-edit two-field pattern (matching students/staff). full_name is kept in sync (first + ' ' + last) on every self-edit, and staff/student edits propagate to users.full_name via the sync triggers, so any consumer reading users.full_name keeps working.

### students

A student record. May or may not be linked to a users row (via user_id for adult students or parent_user_id for kids).

| Column | Type | Null | Default | Notes |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| id | uuid | NO | gen_random_uuid() | PK |
| user_id | uuid | YES | FK users.id | Set when adult student claims profile; also set post kid→adult transition |
| parent_user_id | uuid | YES | FK users.id | Set when parent claims profile (kids); **remains set after transition as guardian read-only access** |
| full_name | text | NO | - | Display name (preserved alongside split first_name/last_name) |
| first_name | text | YES | - | Two-field input post G17 |
| last_name | text | YES | - | Two-field input post G17 |
| belt | text | YES | - | white, blue, purple, brown, black, kids belts (grey/white, grey, grey/black, yellow/white, yellow, yellow/black, orange/white, orange, orange/black, green/white, green, green/black) |
| degree | integer | YES | 0 | Stripes (colored) or degrees (black, capped at 6 in visual) |
| prog | text | YES | 'adult' | adult or kids |
| gi_classes | numeric | YES | 0 | Cached count, derived from attendance SUM (migration 47) |
| nogi_classes | numeric | YES | 0 | Cached count, derived from attendance SUM (migration 47) |
| total | numeric | YES | 0 | Cached total, derived from attendance (SUM of class_value where status='present') (migrations 45/47) |
| grade | numeric | YES | 0 | Classes since last promotion, derived (SUM of class_value since last_marker_date) |
| gi_grade | numeric | YES | 0 | Same as grade, gi-only |
| last_marker_date | date | YES | - | Cached MAX(promotions.date), set by recompute_student_stats. Drives eligibility calc without per-check query on promotions. (migration 45). Trigger added migration 46 to keep this in sync on promotion INSERT. |
| journey | jsonb | YES | [] | Array of milestone objects |
| feedback | jsonb | YES | [] | (legacy field, see feedback table — actual instructor feedback now lives there) |
| notes | text | YES | - | Free-text admin notes |
| unit_id | uuid | YES | FK units.id | Home academy |
| legacy_id | text | YES | - | Stable short ID for URL/reference (e.g., fwb, aar) |
| has_mybjj_gi | boolean | NO | false | Owns branded myBJJ gi (relevant for promotion ceremony — info text only, no gate) (migration 49) |
| gender | text | YES | - | m, f, o, n |
| initials | text | YES | - | Avatar fallback initials |
| photo_url | text | YES | - | Approved photo path |
| email | text | YES | - | Student's login email (adults only; null for kids until transition) |
| date_of_birth | date | YES | - | Required for kids (programme + transition eligibility); optional for adults |
| bjj_start_date | date | YES | - | Optional month-precision date capturing when the student first started practicing BJJ anywhere (independent of joined_at). Drives "Training since" header and the "Started BJJ" first journey entry. Validation: ≤ today and ≤ joined_at. Stored as YYYY-MM-01 (day fixed to 01). (migration 66) |
| phone | text | YES | - | Student's phone (adults). For kids, see parent_phone. |
| weight_kg | integer | YES | - |  |
| height_cm | integer | YES | - |  |
| emergency_contact_name | text | YES | - |  |
| emergency_contact_phone | text | YES | - |  |
| parent_name | text | YES | - | Primary parent name (kids only) |
| parent_phone | text | YES | - | Primary parent phone |
| parent_email | text | YES | - | Primary parent login email |
| parent2_name | text | YES | - | Secondary parent name (optional) |
| parent2_phone | text | YES | - | Secondary parent phone |
| parent2_email | text | YES | - | Secondary parent login email (also gets whitelist entry) |
| social_handles | jsonb | NO | '{}' | Social media handles (Instagram, TikTok, etc) as JSONB keys (migration 49) |
| medical_notes | text | YES | - | Free-text medical/allergy info (migration 52). Surfaced via roster medical badge; editable by admin and parent |
| active | boolean | NO | true | Soft delete / mark inactive |
| created_at | timestamptz | NO | now() |  |

**Critical invariant**: total, gi_classes, nogi_classes, grade, gi_grade are **derived** from the attendance table by recompute_student_stats(student_id) and updated automatically by the trg_attendance_recompute trigger. Never increment these manually. Migration 47 changed types from integer to numeric to support fractional class_value sums.

**Removed columns (historical context):** nickname (Batch 2B), has_gi boolean (in favor of class_type on attendance).

