### attendance

Source of truth for class participation. One row per (student, class_date, class_time).

| Column | Type | Null | Default | Notes |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| id | uuid | NO | gen_random_uuid() | PK |
| student_id | uuid | NO | FK students.id |  |
| class_id | uuid | YES | FK classes.id ON DELETE RESTRICT | Optional reference to recurring class. RESTRICT protects history when class is deleted (migration 43). |
| class_legacy_id | text | YES | - | Alternative class identifier |
| unit_id | uuid | YES | FK units.id | Cached for RLS efficiency |
| class_date | date | YES | - | The day of the class |
| class_time | text | YES | - | HH:MM string |
| class_type | text | YES | - | gi, nogi, etc — drives gi/nogi attribution (migration 48) |
| modality | text | YES | - | Additional categorization of the class style/modality |
| status | text | YES | going | going, present, absent |
| class_value | numeric | NO | 1.00 | 5-tier attendance weight: 2.00 (signature + circle), 1.00 (signature), 0.50 (circle), 0.25 (tick), 0.00 (X). total and grade use SUM(class_value), not COUNT(*). Picker UI pending (G9 Phase 2). (migration 45) |
| gi | boolean | NO | true | Legacy boolean; class_type is the modern signal (migration 48) |
| attended_at | timestamptz | NO | now() | Original timestamp (legacy) |
| checked_in_at | timestamptz | YES | now() | When student initiated check-in |
| confirmed_by | uuid | YES | FK users.id | Instructor who confirmed/denied |
| confirmed_at | timestamptz | YES | - | When status was last changed |
| confirmed_by_instructor_id | uuid | YES | FK staff.id | (legacy, prefer confirmed_by) |

**Unique constraint**: (student_id, class_date, class_time) — one row per student per class.

**Trigger**: trg_attendance_recompute fires AFTER INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE and calls recompute_student_stats(NEW.student_id).

