### staff_notes

Head Instructor Notes (admin → staff). **New table, migration 56.** Moved out of staff.feedback JSONB because that field leaked via the public staff_select policy (anyone can SELECT staff). These notes are sensitive admin-to-staff communication, so they live in a dedicated table with owner-only RLS.

| Column | Type | Null | Default | Notes |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| id | uuid | NO | gen_random_uuid() | PK |
| staff_id | uuid | NO | FK staff.id ON DELETE CASCADE | Subject staff member |
| author_id | uuid | YES | FK users.id | Admin who wrote the note |
| author_name | text | YES | - | Denormalized author display name |
| text | text | NO | - | Free-text note |
| created_at | timestamptz | NO | now() |  |

**RLS:** staff_notes_select is SELECT for authenticated using is_admin() — **owner/instructor-admin read only**. No INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE policies; all writes go through the SECURITY DEFINER RPCs add_staff_note / delete_staff_note. The migration also seeds one historical note for staff legacy_id 'felipe_s' and empties staff.feedback to '[]'.

