### programme_weeks

Curriculum schedule by week. Reworked in the Programme redesign (V1_3): week_start anchors to a real Monday, week_index is the instructor's program-week number.

| Column | Type | Null | Default | Notes |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| id | uuid | NO | gen_random_uuid() | PK |
| unit_id | uuid | YES | FK units.id |  |
| week_start | date | YES | - | Real-calendar Monday anchor. Drives month/year grouping, filtering, and display order |
| week_index | integer | NO | - | The program WEEK number (e.g. "Week 8"). Shown in-app and on the G19 share card. Editable; default max(week_index)+1 |
| theme | text | YES | - | Week theme/focus |
| fundamentals | jsonb | YES | [] | Curriculum items for fundamentals classes |
| mixed | jsonb | YES | [] |  |
| advanced | jsonb | YES | [] |  |
| kids | jsonb | YES | [] | Kids curriculum (Share Kids program template, G19) |
| stand_up | jsonb | YES | [] |  |
| ground | jsonb | YES | [] |  |
| programs | text[] | YES | {} | Which programs apply |
| color | text | YES | - |  |
| notes | text | YES | - |  |
| legacy_id | text | YES | - |  |
| created_at | timestamptz | NO | now() |  |

**Unique constraints:** (unit_id, week_index) and legacy_id. **Note:** the live unique key is (unit_id, week_index), NOT (unit_id, week_start). So the DB enforces "one program-week number per unit", not "one row per Monday per unit" — two rows could share a week_start with different week_index. (The V1_3 plan described a week_start natural key; the implemented constraint is week_index.)

### events

Tournaments, seminars, special events. Embedded in Programme tab today; will move to Activity tab in G21.

| Column | Type | Null | Default | Notes |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| id | uuid | NO | gen_random_uuid() | PK |
| unit_ids | uuid[] | YES | {} | Which units this event applies to (drives visibility scope; written by saveEv from the current unit) |
| unit_legacy_ids | text[] | YES | {} | Legacy mirror |
| title | text | NO | - |  |
| date | date | YES | - |  |
| date_text | text | YES | - | Free-form for ranges ("June 1-3") |
| type | text | YES | - |  |
| description | text | YES | - |  |
| link | text | YES | - | External URL |
| competing_legacy_ids | text[] | YES | {} | Students competing |
| supporting_legacy_ids | text[] | YES | {} | Students attending in support |
| legacy_id | text | YES | - |  |
| created_at | timestamptz | NO | now() |  |

**Participation:** competing/supporting are toggled via the set_event_participation RPC (self-only, atomic), not by direct array writes from the client — this fixes both the RLS block (events write is admin-only) and the read-modify-write race on the arrays.

**G20 future (not yet implemented — confirmed absent from the live schema):** add address + maps link (e.g. events.address, events.maps_url) for a "Directions" affordance. **G21 future:** new table event_results for competition results wall.

### wall_reactions

"Oss" acknowledgements on the Community Wall. **New table (V1_3).** Polymorphic by design so future feed item types (e.g. competition posts, G21) reuse it with no new table. **Not versioned as a migration file** (applied directly in the SQL Editor — see Overview).

| Column | Type | Null | Default | Notes |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| id | uuid | NO | gen_random_uuid() | PK |
| target_type | text | NO | - | Feed item type. V1: 'promotion' |
| target_id | uuid | NO | - | UUID of the target (e.g. promotions.id) |
| reactor_user_id | uuid | NO | - | The user (users.id / auth.uid) who reacted |
| kind | text | NO | 'oss' | Reaction kind. V1: 'oss' |
| created_at | timestamptz | NO | now() |  |

**Unique constraint:** (target_type, target_id, reactor_user_id, kind) — one reaction of a kind per reactor per target.

**RLS:** wall_reactions_select (SELECT) mirrors Wall visibility — approved adult students and staff can read reactions on adult promotions in their unit. No write policies; all writes go through the toggle_oss RPC (atomic, no race), which is adults + staff only (kids' promotions never reactable).

### notifications

Real-time event delivery (migration 42).

| Column | Type | Notes |
| --- | --- | --- |
| id | uuid | PK |
| user_id | uuid NOT NULL | FK users.id ON DELETE CASCADE |
| type | text NOT NULL | check: 'photo_approved' / 'photo_rejected' / 'feedback_received' / 'promotion' / 'admin_message' |
| title | text NOT NULL |  |
| body | text |  |
| related_entity_type | text | check: 'photo_approval' / 'feedback' / 'promotion' / 'admin_message' |
| related_entity_id | uuid | for dedupe + deep-link |
| metadata | jsonb NOT NULL | default {} |
| read_at | timestamptz | null = unread |
| dismissed_at | timestamptz | null = visible; set = removed from inbox (no hard delete) |
| created_at | timestamptz NOT NULL | default now() |

**RLS:** SELECT/UPDATE own row only (notifications_select_own, notifications_update_own). No INSERT/DELETE policies — all writes via SECURITY DEFINER RPCs.

## RLS policies

Every table has Row Level Security enabled. Policies use helper functions on auth.uid(): is_admin(), is_staff(), is_approved(), is_unit_owner(uuid), is_unit_owner_any(), current_role(), current_unit(), current_status().

**Note on current_role():** in policy SQL it is double-quoted ("current_role"()) because current_role is a reserved SQL keyword.

### Policy highlights by table

**users**: own row SELECT/UPDATE/INSERT, admin DELETE (users_select_self, users_update_self, users_insert_self, users_delete_admin).

**students** (students_select, migration 55): admin (all), staff (own unit), self (user_id), parent (parent_user_id — including post-transition guardian), or peer adult in same unit (unit = current_unit() and role = 'student' and prog = 'adult'). Write (students_write ALL): admin or staff in own unit.

**staff**: SELECT public (staff_select — anyone can see who teaches). Write (staff_write ALL): admin only. (Because staff_select is public, sensitive admin notes were moved out of staff.feedback into staff_notes — see migration 56.)

**attendance** (attendance_select, migration 55): admin, or via the student row — self, parent, staff of unit, OR peer adult in same unit but **only for status='going'** (peer adults see who's going, not confirmed present/absent of others). INSERT: admin, staff, self/parent check-in. UPDATE: staff of unit only. DELETE: staff or self/parent for own going-status row.

**promotions**: two SELECT policies, OR-combined:
- promotions_select (migration 55): admin, or via student row — self, parent, or staff of unit.
- promotions_select_adult_peer: lets an approved adult in the unit read other adults' promotions — **this is what powers the Community Wall** (peer-visible adult promotions). Applied directly in the SQL Editor; not in a migration file.
Write (promotions_write ALL): staff.

**feedback**: SELECT visible to admin, owner of relationship, staff of unit. INSERT/UPDATE by staff. DELETE by author or admin (via delete_feedback RPC).

**staff_notes** (migration 56): staff_notes_select is SELECT for authenticated using is_admin() — **owner/instructor-admin read only**. No write policies; writes via add_staff_note / delete_staff_note RPCs.

**wall_reactions**: wall_reactions_select (SELECT) mirrors Wall visibility (approved adults + staff, adult promotions in unit). No write policies; writes via toggle_oss RPC.

**photo_approvals**: SELECT by submitter or admin. INSERT by submitter. UPDATE/DELETE by admin (or self if still pending).

**classes**, **programme_weeks**: SELECT by anyone in the unit. Write by admin or staff of unit (classes_write, programme_write — both ALL).

**events**: SELECT by anyone whose unit is in unit_ids (events_select). Write by admin (events_write ALL). Self participation via set_event_participation RPC.

**whitelist**: All operations admin-only (whitelist_admin ALL).

**units**: SELECT public (units_select). Write by admin (units_write ALL).

**notifications**: SELECT/UPDATE own row only.

## RPCs (Postgres functions)

All callable from client via supabase.rpc('function_name', { args }). Functions marked SECURITY DEFINER run as superuser and bypass RLS — gated by role checks in the body.

### Authentication and identity

**claim_profile() → users** (SECURITY DEFINER). First-auth setup: reads auth.users.email, looks up whitelist, creates users row, links staff/students, syncs has_password, seeds journey. Idempotent. **Migration 59:** also re-links orphan kids — students rows where parent_email or parent2_email matches the signing-in user's email get their parent_user_id populated on every login (covers race conditions where a kid was created before the parent first signed in). **Migration 61:** when the JWT carries no display name, claim_profile derives full_name from the linked record — first tries the user's own student row, then falls back to parent_name from a linked kid's row.

**current_role(), current_unit(), current_status() → text/uuid/text.** Read fields off the caller's users row (used in RLS).

**is_admin(), is_staff(), is_approved(), is_unit_owner(p_unit_id uuid), is_unit_owner_any() → boolean.** Role/ownership helpers.

**email_signin_state(p_email text) → text.** Returns has_password / no_password / not_authorized (prevents enumeration). Drives 2-step login.

**mark_password_set() → void.** Sets users.has_password = true for the caller.

### Staff management

**add_staff_member(p_full_name, p_email, p_belt, p_degree, p_unit_legacy_id, p_initials, p_role) → staff** (SECURITY DEFINER). Admin-only. Creates staff row + whitelist entry.

**edit_staff_admin(p_legacy_id text, p_payload jsonb) → staff** (SECURITY DEFINER). Admin edits any staff. Payload: first_name, last_name, full_name, initials, belt, degree, role_title, email, has_mybjj_gi, social_handles, photo_url.

**edit_staff_self(p_legacy_id text, p_payload jsonb) → staff** (SECURITY DEFINER). Staff edits own row. Per Option B: first_name, last_name, full_name, initials, email, has_mybjj_gi, social_handles, photo_url. **Belt, degree, role_title NOT self-editable.**

**add_staff_note(p_staff_id uuid, p_text text) → setof staff_notes** (SECURITY DEFINER, migration 56). Admin-only. Inserts into the staff_notes table (NOT staff.feedback JSONB anymore). Returns the staff member's notes newest-first.

**delete_staff_note(p_staff_id uuid, p_note_id uuid) → setof staff_notes** (SECURITY DEFINER, migration 56). Admin-only. Deletes by note id from staff_notes. (Signature changed from the old (target_legacy_id, created_at) form.)

**remove_staff(p_legacy_id text) → staff.** Admin-only soft delete (active=false).

**set_staff_email(p_legacy_id text, p_email text) → staff.** Admin-only. Updates email + mirrors to whitelist.

### Student management

**edit_student_self(p_legacy_id text, p_payload jsonb) → students** (SECURITY DEFINER, migration 44, extended migration 67). Adult student edits own profile, or parent edits child's. Validates auth.uid() matches user_id OR parent_user_id. Allowed: first_name, last_name, full_name, initials, date_of_birth, **bjj_start_date** (migration 67), phone, gender, weight_kg, height_cm, emergency_contact_name, emergency_contact_phone, has_mybjj_gi, social_handles, photo_url, medical_notes. **Excluded (admin-only):** belt, degree, journey, prog, unit_id, active.

**Clear semantics:** most fields use `COALESCE(p_payload->>'col', col)` so the existing value is preserved when the key is absent from the payload. bjj_start_date uses `CASE WHEN p_payload ? 'bjj_start_date' THEN NULLIF(p_payload->>'bjj_start_date','')::date ELSE bjj_start_date END` — this lets the field be CLEARED by sending an empty string in the payload, while still preserving the value when the key is omitted. Same pattern as weight_kg / height_cm / has_mybjj_gi / social_handles. Migration 67 was a stand-alone follow-up to extend the whitelist after the bjj_start_date column landed in migration 66.

**recompute_student_stats(p_student_id uuid) → void** (SECURITY DEFINER, rewritten migrations 45/47/48). Recomputes total, gi_classes, nogi_classes, grade, gi_grade as SUM(class_value) where status='present'; caches last_marker_date = MAX(promotions.date).

**seed_student_journey_if_empty(p_student_id uuid) → void.** Adds the "Joined myBJJ app" entry if journey is empty.

**update_class_counts(...) → students** (DEPRECATED, legacy). Superseded by recompute; should not be used.

### Kids privacy

**kids_unit_summary() → jsonb** (SECURITY DEFINER, migration 57). Returns a NON-identifying aggregate of the kids program in the caller's unit: { total, by_belt: [{belt, count}] }. Never returns rows / names / photos. Authorized for parent, staff, or admin (approved). Backs the kids-program summary parents see without breaching other kids' privacy.

### Events

**set_event_participation(p_event_id uuid, p_status text) → (events)** (SECURITY DEFINER). Any approved unit member marks their OWN participation (competing / supporting / none). Resolves the caller to a student or staff legacy_id and updates events.competing_legacy_ids / supporting_legacy_ids atomically on the server — fixing the RLS block (events write is admin-only) and the read-modify-write race. Applied directly in the SQL Editor; not in a migration file.

### Community Wall

**toggle_oss(p_target_type text, p_target_id uuid) → jsonb** (SECURITY DEFINER). Toggles the caller's "Oss" on a feed target, returning { count, reacted }. Gated: authenticated, approved, role in (student, owner, admin), target_type='promotion', and the target must be a visible adult promotion in the caller's unit (kids excluded). Atomic insert/delete on wall_reactions. Applied directly in the SQL Editor; not in a migration file.

### Family management (V1 future — NOT YET IN DB)

**add_family(...)** — admin family registration (parent + kids + optional secondary guardian). Confirmed absent from the live schema; pending implementation.

### Kid → adult transition (V1 future — NOT YET IN DB)

**transition_kid_to_adult(...)** — manual kid→adult transition. Confirmed absent from the live schema; pending implementation.

### Email and account

**admin_change_user_email(p_target_kind text, p_target_db_id uuid, p_new_email text) → void** (SECURITY DEFINER). Admin changes a student/staff email; updates students/staff.email, users.email, whitelist.email in one transaction. Owner cross-unit; instructor same-unit.

### Feedback

**delete_feedback(p_feedback_id uuid) → void** (SECURITY DEFINER, migration 51). Admin OR original author. Dismisses related notification before DELETE (cascade pattern).

### Photo workflow

**reject_photo(p_id uuid, p_reason text) → photo_approvals.** Admin rejects a pending photo with optional reason. (Approve uses direct UPDATE on status; trg_photo_approval_sync propagates photo_url.)

### Notifications (migration 42)

**Internal (SECURITY DEFINER, revoked from authenticated):**
- create_notification(p_user_id, p_type, p_title, p_body, p_related_entity_type, p_related_entity_id, p_metadata, p_check_prefs) → uuid. Dedupes on (user, type, related_entity) when entity_id set AND not dismissed.
- user_wants_notification_type(p_user_id, p_type) → boolean.

**Public (authenticated):**
- list_my_notifications(p_limit, p_include_dismissed) → setof notifications (default 50, max 200)
- unread_notification_count() → int
- mark_notification_read(p_id) → void (idempotent)
- mark_all_notifications_read() → int
- dismiss_notification(p_id) → void (sets dismissed_at + read_at)
- send_admin_message(p_audience, p_target_user_id, p_title, p_body) → int. Audiences: all_unit, all_adults, all_kids, specific_user. Gated by is_staff() OR is_unit_owner_any(). Cap 200 recipients.

## Triggers

**trg_attendance_recompute** on attendance — AFTER INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE → attendance_recompute_trigger() → recompute_student_stats().

**trg_promotions_recompute** on promotions — AFTER INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE → promotions_recompute_trigger() → recompute_student_stats(). Keeps last_marker_date fresh. (Migration 46; now fires on all mutations, not just INSERT.)

**trg_photo_approval_sync** on photo_approvals — AFTER UPDATE → sync_photo_url_on_approval(). Propagates approved photo_url to users/students/staff.

**trg_notify_photo_status_change** on photo_approvals — AFTER UPDATE OF status → photo_approved/photo_rejected notification. check_prefs=false.

**trg_notify_feedback_added** on feedback — AFTER INSERT → feedback_received notification. check_prefs=true ('feedback').

**trg_notify_promotion** on promotions — AFTER INSERT → promotion notification ('New belt!' / 'New stripe!'). check_prefs=true ('promotions').

**trg_sync_user_full_name_from_staff** on staff — AFTER UPDATE → sync_user_full_name_from_staff(). Keeps users.full_name in sync when a staff name changes.

**trg_sync_user_full_name_from_student** on students — AFTER UPDATE → sync_user_full_name_from_student(). Keeps users.full_name in sync when a student name changes.

**trg_relink_orphan_kids** on users — AFTER INSERT → re-links any students rows whose parent_email or parent2_email matches NEW.email. Belt-and-suspenders companion to claim_profile's re-link logic (migration 60). Fires on every new public.users insert so orphan kids attach to a freshly-created parent the moment that parent's users row appears.

## Operational notes

### Migrations

All schema changes happen via SQL migration files in supabase/NN_phase8_*.sql. Migrations are idempotent (IF NOT EXISTS, ON CONFLICT DO UPDATE) so they're safe to re-run.

**Current migration set on filesystem (validated):** 01 through 67, with gaps at 07 and 38 (unused numbers, not deletions).

Migration log (recent batches):

- **42** — Notifications (G1): table + 7 RPCs + 3 triggers
- **43** — Classes CRUD (G4): attendance.class_id FK ON DELETE RESTRICT
- **44** — Name sync (G2): edit_student_self SECURITY DEFINER RPC
- **45** — Promotion eligibility (G9.1): attendance.class_value numeric + students.last_marker_date + recompute SUM(class_value)
- **46** — Promotions recompute trigger
- **47** — Numeric stats: students.total/gi_classes/nogi_classes/grade/gi_grade integer → numeric
- **48** — Gi/nogi attribution via class_type
- **49** — Profile fields: students/staff has_mybjj_gi + social_handles
- **50** — Staff alignment (G17.2b): edit_staff_self/admin rewrite
- **51** — Delete cascade (G17.2d): delete_staff_note + delete_feedback with notification dismissal
- **52** — Parent Architecture V1 schema (G14.2): units.phone/mobile_phone/email, users.welcome_dismissed, students.medical_notes + Neutral Bay contact seed
- **53** — users.phone (parent self-managed contact)
- **54** — users name split: users.first_name + last_name (backfill from full_name; full_name kept canonical)
- **55** — RLS privacy hardening (child-safety): rewrote students_select / promotions_select / attendance_select (peer adults see only status='going' on others)
- **56** — staff_notes table: moved Head Instructor Notes out of staff.feedback (leaked via public staff_select) into an owner-only table; add_staff_note / delete_staff_note rewritten; staff.feedback emptied
- **57** — kids_unit_summary RPC: non-identifying kids-program aggregate (counts only)
- **58** — kid_creation_link_parent: kid creation now resolves parent_user_id from parent_email/parent2_email up front (covers admin-creates-kid-before-parent-signs-in flow)
- **59** — claim_relink_kids: claim_profile() re-links orphan kids on every authentication (students rows where parent_email or parent2_email matches the signing-in user)
- **60** — relink_trigger: trg_relink_orphan_kids on public.users — belt-and-suspenders companion to claim_profile's re-link, fires on every new users row insert
- **61** — claim_name_fallback: claim_profile() derives full_name when JWT carries no display name — first the user's own student row, then parent_name from a linked kid
- **62** — promotions_correction_type: extends the promotions.type CHECK to include 'correction' alongside 'belt' / 'stripe'
- **63** — attendance_integrity: tightens attendance write paths (status transitions, idempotency, foreign-key integrity) to prevent stale "going" rows from outliving the class they reference
- **64** — going_orphan_cleanup: removes orphan 'going' attendance rows for classes that have been deleted or whose class_date has passed without confirmation
- **65** — kids_privacy_hardening: tighter privacy on kids data (peer roster restrictions, photo visibility constraints, RLS adjustments) shipped during the E1/E2/E3 batches
- **66** — bjj_start_date: adds students.bjj_start_date date (idempotent ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS). Optional month-precision date for when the student first started practicing BJJ; surfaces in profile header "Training since" and as the first journey entry "Started BJJ"
- **67** — edit_student_self_bjj: extends edit_student_self RPC whitelist to accept bjj_start_date using the CASE WHEN NULLIF clear-support pattern (lets parent / student / staff clear the field by sending empty string while preserving when the key is omitted)

### Unversioned live objects (not in migration files)

Applied directly in the Supabase SQL Editor during the Community/Wall/Oss arc (V1_3), with no numbered file:

- table **wall_reactions** + policy **wall_reactions_select**
- policy **promotions_select_adult_peer** (powers the Wall)
- RPC **toggle_oss(text, uuid)**
- RPC **set_event_participation(uuid, text)**

**Risk:** a fresh database built from the migration files alone (e.g. mybjj-staging) will be missing all of the above. **Backlog (before staging):** capture each as a numbered migration (58+).

### Pending migrations (V1 future)

- **add_family RPC** — Mario/instructor adds family in single flow
- **transition_kid_to_adult RPC** — manual kid→adult transition
- **events.address / events.maps_url** — G20 directions/maps
- **event_results table** — G21 competition results wall

(units.phone/mobile_phone/email, users.welcome_dismissed, and students.medical_notes — previously pending — landed in migration 52.)

### Backup

Free Supabase plan has no automatic project backup. Manual snapshots via pg_dump stored in ~/mybjj-backups/.

